Data availability

            The grid-cell-level fire and lightning season definitions—including both initiation and cessation days of the year (1–365) and the length as the total number of days—as well as any related statistics developed as part of this project are freely available from the University of Tasmania Research Data Portal92 (https://doi.org/10.25959/2hnc-rz89). The original ecoregion vector dataset48 is available from the World Wildlife Fund (https://www.worldwildlife.org/publications/terrestrial-ecoregions-of-the-world). The preprocessed gridded ERA5 reanalysis data28,84 are publicly hosted on Google Drive (https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1WWlDZ2lL941TzJAL7xubrJproQuskksA). The WWLLN Global Lightning Climatology86 release is available via Zenodo at https://zenodo.org/records/10725446(ref. 93) and updated annually. Data from WHAM!89 are also available via Zenodo at https://zenodo.org/records/13834239 (ref. 94), with the scripts used to create the data hosted on GitHub (https://github.com/OliPerkins1987/Wildfire_Human_Agency_Model). The MODIS MCD64A1 burned area87 product is available from the University of Maryland SFTP server (fuoco.geog.umd.edu). We originally retrieved the MOD17A3HGF net primary production90 product using wget from the USGS server (e4ftl01.cr.usgs.gov/MOLT/MOD17A3HGF.061/), but this method is no longer feasible since the MOD17A3HGF product migrated to a new OPeNDAP repository on 30 June 2025 (https://opendap.cr.usgs.gov/opendap/hyrax/DP137/MOLT/MOD17A3HGF.061/). All links provided in this statement reflect availability as of 23 July 2025.
